content:
Use Underwriter Console to give underwriters easy access to the loan application details so that they can make informed decisions. 

Underwriters can get a consolidated view of a submitted loan application on the application form product record page. Users view and edit assets, liabilities, and collateral details, assign action items, confirm pricing, verify integration results, such as Know Your Customer and credit checks, and approve or reject an application.

The Underwriter Console is configured with FlexCards that enable underwriters to review and verify a loan application and supporting documentation, define loan terms, customize an offer, and complete the stages of a loan application.

FlexCards and components included in the Underwriter Console:

* DigitalLendingApplicantDetailCard
* DigitalLendingApplicantProfileCard
* DigitalLendingOfferDetailCard
* DigitalLendingSellerItemDetails
* DigitalLendingLoanDocuments

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions. 

Create a permission set that grants users access to the Digital Lending Underwriter Console features.

The Underwriter Console provides a streamlined view of the loan application details without switching between tools.
title: Underwriter Console for Digital Lending
